ggbnec_data

Source: R/ggbnec.R
ggbnec_data.Rd

Creates the data.frame that feeds into the plotting function ggbnec.

ggbnec_data(x, add_nec = TRUE, add_ecx = FALSE, ...)

Arguments

x

An object of class bayesnecfit or bayesmanecfit, as returned by function bnec.
add_nec

Should NEC values be added to the plot? Defaults to TRUE.
add_ecx

Should ECx values be added to the plot? Defaults to FALSE.
...

Additional arguments to be passed to ecx. By default, function ecx returns EC10.

Value

A data.frame.

Examples

# \donttest{
library(brms)
library(bayesnec)
options(mc.cores = 2)
data(nec_data)

test <- bnec(data = nec_data, x_var = "x", y_var = "y",
             model = c("nec3param", "nec4param"), iter = 2e2,
             family = Beta(link = "identity"))
